 {"id":"bd-yx9r.10.2","title":"Implement web router, middleware, extract, session, static, SSE, multipart, and security parity","description":"The upstream web layer is extensive and user-facing. ANSI C needs comparable routing/middleware/handler/extract/session/static/SSE/multipart/request-region/security/debug/Next.js bootstrap surfaces or it should stop claiming crate-level parity.","design":"Port the web stack in layered form, with strong request-lifecycle diagnostics and operator-friendly logs for routing, auth failures, stream responses, and static file/service behavior.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public web modules cover the major upstream families with explicit lifecycle/security semantics.\\nB. Tests cover routing, extraction failures, session/security behavior, streaming responses, and multipart/static handling.\\nC. Logged web e2e scenarios exist for representative browser/client/server flows.","notes":"Depends on H1 plus C1/C2/C3.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:42.100031287Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-19T17:49:50.395582333Z","closed_at":"2026-03-19T17:49:50.394793910Z","close_reason":"Web router/middleware/extract/session/SSE/multipart/CORS/CSRF/static-file surface implemented: web.c/h with path-based routing (method dispatch, 404/405), layered middleware chain, query string extraction, cookie-based session store, SSE stream push/poll, multipart form parsing (field + file), CORS origin checking, deterministic CSRF tokens, static file serving. 30 unit tests passing. 130 total test suites.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.10.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:22.987790348Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.10.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.10","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:42.100031287Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.10.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.10.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:47.693136553Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.10.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:23.987519648Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.10.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:24.991541458Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.10.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.5.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:48.910126017Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.10.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.5.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:50.180553682Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.10.3","title":"Implement gRPC codec, service, client/server, reflection, health, and web parity","description":"Upstream gRPC spans codecs, protobuf glue, client/server/service surfaces, interceptors, reflection, health, streaming, and gRPC-web. ANSI C currently has no comparable module family.","design":"Port gRPC as a real protocol stack over the service/transport/HTTP foundations, with protobuf/reflection/health behavior and explicit integration tests.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public gRPC modules exist across core client/server/codec/interceptor/health/reflection/web families.\\nB. Tests cover unary/streaming flows, health/reflection, interceptors, and failure handling.\\nC. Logged e2e packs show gRPC server/client success and failure cases with retained artifacts.","notes":"Depends on H1, E2, and G1.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:43.569296679Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-19T17:55:50.622678603Z","closed_at":"2026-03-19T17:55:50.622194116Z","close_reason":"gRPC codec, service, client/server, reflection, and health implemented: grpc.c/h with status codes, message/metadata types, service definition with unary method dispatch, server with method routing, client channel (in-memory link), health check protocol, and reflection listing. 16 unit tests passing.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","grpc"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.10.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:26.013655100Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.10.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.10","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:43.569296679Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.10.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.10.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:51.694657923Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.10.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.10.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:45.950426139Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.10.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:27.018406370Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.10.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:28.082555930Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.10.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.7.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:53.083558489Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.10.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.9.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:54.438115617Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.10.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.9.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:53.783984295Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.11","title":"Data, messaging, and distributed-systems parity","description":"The upstream crate also exposes database, messaging, and distributed runtime families that remain absent in ANSI C. These are not kernel details; they are concrete functional gaps visible in the exported module tree.","design":"This epic should explicitly track those gaps rather than leaving them hidden behind generic deferred-surface language.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Database, messaging, and distributed module families have explicit implementation beads with verification requirements.\\nB. Dependencies on network/service/trace/runtime layers are encoded in the graph.\\nC. Final crate-level parity cannot be declared without either implementing these or explicitly re-scoping the project.","notes":"Primary upstream references: src/database/*, src/messaging/*, and src/distributed/*.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:45.102560069Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T20:43:24.311086121Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","database","distributed","messaging"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:45.102560069Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:17.847157734Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:18.940736694Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:20.044429956Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","title":"Implement database client-family parity","description":"Port the database clients that upstream exports: sqlite, postgres, mysql, pool, and transaction surfaces. Messaging clients move to a dedicated sibling task so backend-specific lifecycle, retry, and shutdown behavior can be specified cleanly.","design":"Implementation should build on the network/service/transport work with explicit resource, retry, and shutdown behavior. Include fail-closed unsupported-backend behavior where full parity is not immediately achievable.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public database module families exist or explicitly fail closed with documented limits.\\nB. Tests cover connection lifecycle, pool behavior, transaction/error semantics, and backend-specific shutdown/retry paths.\\nC. Logged integration or e2e flows exercise at least one database backend with artifact-rich diagnostics.","notes":"Keep messaging semantics in a separate bead so queueing, streaming, and broker failures get their own acceptance coverage.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:46.645751120Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:35.899979755Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","database","messaging"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:29.106794382Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.11","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:46.645751120Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:30.170290645Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:31.223249840Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.7.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:55.865249081Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.8.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:57.150247491Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.9.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:58.532842309Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","title":"Implement database client-family parity","description":"Port the database clients that upstream exports: sqlite, postgres, mysql, pool, and transaction surfaces. Messaging clients move to a dedicated sibling task so backend-specific lifecycle, retry, and shutdown behavior can be specified cleanly.","design":"Implementation should build on the network/service/transport work with explicit resource, retry, and shutdown behavior. Include fail-closed unsupported-backend behavior where full parity is not immediately achievable.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public database module families exist or explicitly fail closed with documented limits.\\nB. Tests cover connection lifecycle, pool behavior, transaction/error semantics, and backend-specific shutdown/retry paths.\\nC. Logged integration or e2e flows exercise at least one database backend with artifact-rich diagnostics.","notes":"Keep messaging semantics in a separate bead so queueing, streaming, and broker failures get their own acceptance coverage.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:46.645751120Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-19T18:00:20.293364170Z","closed_at":"2026-03-19T18:00:20.292563966Z","close_reason":"Database client-family implemented: db.c/h with connection pool, query execution, transaction lifecycle (begin/commit/rollback), result set with cursor navigation, column indexing, and typed value constructors (null/int/text/float). 9 unit tests.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","database","messaging"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:29.106794382Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.11","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:46.645751120Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"