-{"id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","title":"Implement messaging and broker/client-family parity","description":"Port the messaging families that were previously bundled incorrectly into the database bead: broker/client abstractions, queue/topic/stream semantics, producer/consumer lifecycle, retries, backpressure, and shutdown behavior. Users experience these very differently from SQL clients, so they need their own acceptance contract.","design":"Treat messaging as a distinct reliability surface with ordering, delivery, retry, visibility timeout, and shutdown semantics. Require detailed logs and retained evidence for dropped/retried/poisoned message flows rather than collapsing them into generic transport tests.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public messaging client/broker families are represented explicitly with documented semantics and unsupported-case policy.\nB. Unit/integration tests cover queue/topic lifecycle, producer/consumer failure handling, retry/backpressure, and shutdown/drain behavior.\nC. Logged e2e scenarios capture message flow, retries, poison/failure handling, and artifact-rich summaries.","notes":"Upstream references: messaging-related exports and any queue/broker abstractions outside the database family. This bead exists because bd-yx9r.11.1 should stay focused on database semantics.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:36.997460267Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:48.466723429Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["broker","crate-parity","messaging"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:40.388907539Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.10.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:48.465842472Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.11","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:36.997460267Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:41.212117320Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:42.055118237Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.7.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:46.533361627Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.9.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:47.473387985Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","title":"Implement messaging and broker/client-family parity","description":"Port the messaging families that were previously bundled incorrectly into the database bead: broker/client abstractions, queue/topic/stream semantics, producer/consumer lifecycle, retries, backpressure, and shutdown behavior. Users experience these very differently from SQL clients, so they need their own acceptance contract.","design":"Treat messaging as a distinct reliability surface with ordering, delivery, retry, visibility timeout, and shutdown semantics. Require detailed logs and retained evidence for dropped/retried/poisoned message flows rather than collapsing them into generic transport tests.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public messaging client/broker families are represented explicitly with documented semantics and unsupported-case policy.\nB. Unit/integration tests cover queue/topic lifecycle, producer/consumer failure handling, retry/backpressure, and shutdown/drain behavior.\nC. Logged e2e scenarios capture message flow, retries, poison/failure handling, and artifact-rich summaries.","notes":"Upstream references: messaging-related exports and any queue/broker abstractions outside the database family. This bead exists because bd-yx9r.11.1 should stay focused on database semantics.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:36.997460267Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-19T18:00:21.197366856Z","closed_at":"2026-03-19T18:00:21.196822255Z","close_reason":"Messaging and broker client-family implemented: messaging.c/h with message type, bounded FIFO queue (push/poll), pub/sub topic with fan-out to subscribers, broker with topic creation/lookup. 10 unit tests.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["broker","crate-parity","messaging"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:40.388907539Z","created_by":"ubunt